Definition: an alkaloid with anticholinergic effects that is used as a sedative and to treat nausea and to dilate the pupils in ophthalmic procedures
Example: transdermal scopolamine is used to treat motion sickness; someone sedated with scopolamine has difficulty lying
Synonyms: hyoscine, noun, substance, alkaloid, an, with, anticholinergic, effects, that, is, used, as, a, sedative, and, to, treat, nausea, dilate, the, pupils, in, ophthalmic, procedures, transdermal, motion, sickness, someone, sedated, has, difficulty, lying
Category: noun.artifact
